---
const points = [
  {
    k: 'you hold the keys',
    body: 'Your provider token is read from your machine and used to call the provider API directly. Nothing phones home.',
  },
  {
    k: 'firewall at create',
    body: 'roostr creates the tagged firewall before the droplet, so the network policy is in effect from the first packet. Port 22 is never briefly exposed.',
  },
  {
    k: 'on-box ufw layer',
    body: 'A second firewall inside the box restricts SSH to the tailscale0 interface only.',
  },
  {
    k: 'zero public inbound',
    body: 'You reach the box exclusively over your tailnet with key-only OpenSSH through MagicDNS. No Tailscale SSH daemon, standard sshd only.',
  },
  {
    k: 'no sudo for dev',
    body: 'An agent running arbitrary shell cannot escalate to root, alter the firewall, or exfiltrate host credentials. Root login and password auth are disabled.',
  },
  {
    k: 'no orphan billing',
    body: 'A droplet is recorded the instant it exists, so a failed provision is never an untracked, silently-billing orphan.',
  },
  {
    k: 'scoped tailnet acl',
    body: 'The shipped ACL scopes tag:devbox to your own devices and is never a source, so a compromised box cannot pivot across your tailnet.',
  },
  {
    k: 'minimal metadata',
    body: 'The only secret reaching the box via cloud-init is a single-use Tailscale key that expires in 30 minutes. Clone tokens travel over SSH, never into metadata.',
  },
];
---

<section id="security" class="section divide sec">
  <div class="sec-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="sec-head" data-reveal>
      <span class="kicker">security model</span>
      <h2>An agent on the box can run shell. It still can't hurt you.</h2>
      <p>
        roostr's threat model assumes the agent is untrusted. Every layer is
        designed so arbitrary shell on the box stays contained.
      </p>
    </header>

    <ul class="ledger">
      {points.map((p, i) => (
        <li class="point" data-reveal style={`--reveal-delay:${(i % 2) * 70}ms`}>
          <span class="tick" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 8.5l3.2 3.2L13 4.5" stroke="var(--sage)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3>{p.k}</h3>
            <p>{p.body}</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sec { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .sec-glow {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 -30% auto -30%;
    height: 60%;
    background: radial-gradient(50% 100% at 70% 0%, var(--ember-glow), transparent 65%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .sec-head { position: relative; max-width: 34ch; margin-bottom: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); }
  .sec-head h2 { font-size: var(--step-3); margin: 0.7rem 0 1rem; }
  .sec-head p { color: var(--dawn-dim); font-size: 0.98rem; }

  .ledger {
    position: relative;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--ink-line-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .point {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    padding: clamp(1.1rem, 2.4vw, 1.6rem);
    background: var(--ink);
  }
  .tick {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: 7px;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--sage) 14%, var(--ink-raised));
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .point h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--dawn);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .point p { color: var(--dawn-dim); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.55; }

  @media (max-width: 680px) {
    .ledger { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
